Water at 40.75 feet. Blustery day. A lot of submerged ground starting to emerge from the water. Very few yellow rumped warblers.
Water at 41.5 feet . -Only walked southern half of pond area for complete checklist. Northern half of pond saw further 3 mallards, cedar waxwings and robin.
Water level at 42 feet.

Water level 41.25 feet. Only two flickers, very quiet. Hooded mergansers seem to have left. -Saw two adjacent sparrows in pollinator garden. Identical size, yellow bill, belly coloration, head white bands, but one had distinct white throat. Didn't see yellow on head of white throated. But may have been subtle. Tentative conclusion that one was a hybrid white crowned x white throated sparrow.
Female wood duck investigating nest box at South pond. Water level 41.75 feet.

Large flocks of Canada geese landed in central pond. About 2/3rds large Canada geese, the rest much smaller cackling geese. Likely transient flock as haven't seen cackling geese or this many geese before at West pond. Numbers a guess due to obstructing views and due to some geese being intermediate in size.
